cted to skip the 4.40 metres height attempt, electing to enter at 4.55.\", \"from\": 484, \"to\": 618, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The reigning world indoor champion\", \"from\": 484, \"to\": 518}, {\"ngram\": \"the only entrant\", \"from\": 523, \"to\": 539}, {\"ngram\": \"the 4.40 metres height attempt\", \"from\": 560, \"to\": 590}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a decision that proved costly when she failed to clear the bar with her three tries, particularly after it turned out 4.40 was all it took for nine other women to advance.\", \"from\": 620, \"to\": 798, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a decision\", \"from\": 627, \"to\": 637}, {\"ngram\": \"the bar\", \"from\": 682, \"to\": 689}, {\"ngram\": \"her three tries\", \"from\": 695, \"to\": 710}, {\"ngram\": \"nine other women\", \"from\": 770, \"to\": 786}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She told BBC Radio 5 Live: \\\"It's honestly heart-breaking.\", \"from\": 800, \"to\": 857, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 809, \"end\": 825, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Radio_5_Live\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"BBC Radio 5 Live\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Radio_5_Live\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BBC_Radio_5_Live\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Not the experience I was hoping for and I am so sorry for everyone back home.\", \"from\": 859, \"to\": 937, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"\\\"Not the experience\", \"from\": 859, \"to\": 878}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 918, \"to\": 926}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I wish I could have done better, but I am going to try learn from this and I will take everything I can from it.\", \"from\": 938, \"to\": 1050, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 1025, \"to\": 1035}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I felt great, the best shape of my life.\", \"from\": 1052, \"to\": 1093, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the best shape\", \"from\": 1067, \"to\": 1081}, {\"ngram\": \"my life\", \"from\": 1085, \"to\": 1092}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I did not feel too nervous I love a big crowd.\", \"from\": 1094, \"to\": 1140, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a big crowd\", \"from\": 1128, \"to\": 1139}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not know why, but it wasn't my day and I will use this as an experience to learn from it and to try move on.\", \"from\": 1141, \"to\": 1254, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my day\", \"from\": 1174, \"to\": 1180}, {\"ngram\": \"an experience\", \"from\": 1204, \"to\": 1217}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Thank you to everyone for their support.\\\"\", \"from\": 1256, \"to\": 1298, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 1270, \"to\": 1278}, {\"ngram\": \"their support\", \"from\": 1283, \"to\": 1296}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Caudery is a hugely popular athlete amongst the British team both past and present, many singling her out as one to watch inParis.\", \"from\": 1300, \"to\": 1430, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1348, \"end\": 1355, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.5364841054424098, \"rank\": 0.8204965474869227, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Caudery\", \"from\": 1300, \"to\": 1307}, {\"ngram\": \"a hugely popular athlete\", \"from\": 1311, \"to\": 1335}, {\"ngram\": \"inParis\", \"from\": 1422, \"to\": 1429}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Coming into these Games, she was certainly a strong contender for the podium, if not Olympic gold.\", \"from\": 1432, \"to\": 1530, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these Games\", \"from\": 1444, \"to\": 1455}, {\"ngram\": \"a strong contender\", \"from\": 1475, \"to\": 1493}, {\"ngram\": \"the podium\", \"from\": 1498, \"to\": 1508}, {\"ngram\": \"if not Olympic gold\", \"from\": 1510, \"to\": 1529}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In June, the 24-year-old set a new British record with a personal best of 4.92 in Toulouse - the world-leading mark heading into these Olympics - but was well off the mark in Paris, where she did not get enough forward momentum with her final chance, clipping the bar with her foot as she descended.\", \"from\": 1532, \"to\": 1831, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1567, \"end\": 1581, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Progression_of_the_British_football_transfer_fee_record\", \"score\": 0.9999999029432776, \"rank\": 9.705670502102489e-08, \"text\": \"British record\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Progression_of_the_British_football_transfer_fee_record\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Progression_of_the_British_football_transfer_fee_record\"}, {\"begin\": 1707, \"end\": 1712, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999998181, \"rank\": 1.6744780968000361e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"June\", \"from\": 1535, \"to\": 1539}, {\"ngram\": \"Toulouse\", \"from\": 1614, \"to\": 1622}, {\"ngram\": \"the world-leading mark\", \"from\": 1625, \"to\": 1647}, {\"ngram\": \"these Olympics\", \"from\": 1661, \"to\": 1675}, {\"ngram\": \"the mark\", \"from\": 1695, \"to\": 1703}, {\"ngram\": \"enough forward momentum\", \"from\": 1736, \"to\": 1759}, {\"ngram\": \"her final chance\", \"from\": 1765, \"to\": 1781}, {\"ngram\": \"the bar\", \"from\": 1792, \"to\": 1799}, {\"ngram\": \"her foot\", \"from\": 1805, \"to\": 1813}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Truro athlete entered the Games ranked world number three, behind Australia's Nina Kennedy and the United States' Katie Moon, who memorably shared gold at the 2023 world championships in Budapest.\", \"from\"